    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for devices that convert incoming television signals into the original images and their associated sounds. The receiver contains an amplifier and demodulator of the radio signal; in modern televisions, the receiver may be housed in a unit separate from the monitor</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
